nutrition.title: Mini Pumpkin Donuts
nutrition.summary: Mini Pumpkin Donuts is a breakfast that serves 38. For 11 cents per serving, this recipe covers 2% of your daily requirements of vitamins and minerals. One serving contains 65 calories, 1g of protein, and 1g of fat. 1 person were glad they tried this recipe. From preparation to the plate, this recipe takes about 45 minutes. This recipe from Foodista requires nutmeg, pumpkin, salt, and non-fat milk. All things considered, we decided this recipe deserves a spoonacular score of 9%. This score is very bad (but still fixable). Users who liked this recipe also liked Baked Mini Pumpkin Donuts, Baked Mini Pumpkin Donuts, and Pumpkin Spice Mini-Donuts.
